  "texts": [
    "However, the focus of these reviews has usually been rather broad.",
    "In an attempt to cover the entire field of XAI, they included all types of XAI methods used on all types of data.",
    "Moreover, most reviews assessed the effects of XAI on humans in a variety of dependent variables, including subjective ratings of trust or XAI quality as well as measures of understanding.",
    "Such broad reviews necessarily have to remain superficial regarding the effects of specific types of XAI on specific aspects of human-AI interaction.",
    "Accordingly, previous reviews usually did not include more than a handful of studies that investigated how saliency maps affect human performance in the context of image classification."
  ],
